    "description": "MIT Mini Cheetah — Sangbae Kim's research-grade quasi-direct-drive quadruped (Biomimetic Robotics Lab, MIT, 2018), as expressed in chvmp/champ's open-source URDF for the Mini Cheetah variant. ~9 kg, ~40 cm body length. Tier 2 QDD actuators (MIT in-house design; equivalent torque density to Moteus). Three-DoF leg per corner: hip_roll → hip_pitch → knee_pitch, terminating in a fixed pointed foot. Walking-only mode; designed for high-speed dynamic locomotion (up to ~3.7 m/s in published benchmarks). Geometry adapted from the chvmp/robots Mini Cheetah URDF.",
